{"url": "http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2016/06/24/combating-the-misery-of-menstruation-for-afghan-girls_n_10658244.html", "date": "2016-06-24", "content": "Zahra was in third grade when her period started. At the time, she and her family were in Iran, having fled civil war in their homeland of Afghanistan. Like other Afghan refugees, Zahra and her family endured discrimination and prejudice, and were blamed for bringing illnesses into Iran. When Zahra saw the blood on her underwear, she was convinced she was sick. Could it be cancer? In Zahra\u2019s neighborhood, Iranians associated cancer with Afghans. Would she have to drop out of school?\u00a0Worse, was she dying?\n\u00a0", "title": "Combating the Misery of Menstruation for Afghan Girls"}